1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:52,479
Mr. Narathon, Mr. Phum.

2
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,480
Don't go, Kaimook.

3
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,639
Look at yourself.

4
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,879
You're as pale as a corpse.

5
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,880
And you still say you're fine?

6
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,480
I'm sorry.

7
00:03:57,880 --> 00:03:58,880
Then, please.

8
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,919
Please.

9
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,120
Slowly, please.

10
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:05,800
Please.

11
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,279
She may still be in shock.

12
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:12,359
But overall, there's nothing
to be concerned about.

13
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:16,000
Someone will come shortly
to move her to a patient room.

14
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:17,680
Thank you.

15
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:26,239
Could you please fill out the patient's
information at the front desk?

16
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,160
Of course.

17
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,160
What's your name?

18
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:39,799
Oh, she's already asleep.
She must be exhausted.

19
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:40,920
Please take care of her.

20
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:07,919
I can't believe

21
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:10,560
we're back here chilling like this.

22
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,159
Man,

23
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:22,480
honestly, I don't want
to meddle in your business.

24
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:26,880
What are you trying to say?

25
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,560
Well.

26
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,920
I understand how you feel,

27
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:36,080
but I can't help
worrying about your father.

28
00:05:37,280 --> 00:05:40,399
He looked exhausted.
He even fainted and fell into the water,

29
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:43,839
and then still had to drive
all the way back to Bangkok.

30
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:47,960
You should've let him
stay here and rest first.

31
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:53,320
Someone like him
doesn't break that easily.

32
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,679
I know

33
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:04,720
you and your father don't get along.

34
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,839
But if he hadn't come to help us,

35
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,600
we'd have been in serious trouble.

36
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:36,040
Maybe he intended to help someone else.

37
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,040
We just happened to benefit from it.

38
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,760
What do you mean?

39
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:46,360
I'm going to check on the fish.

40
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,080
Take your time.

41
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:09,959
The woman!

42
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:11,599
Where's the woman?

43
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,319
- Where is she?
- What woman?!

44
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:15,439
You threw her into the sea!

45
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:17,879
- You threw her into the sea!
- Let me go!

46
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,520
Damn it!

47
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:23,479
You threw her into the sea!

48
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,879
- You threw her into the sea!
- You're crazy!

49
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,680
- You threw her into the sea!
- Got a loose mouth, don't you?

50
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,639
Huh?

51
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:31,600
You got such a loose mouth.

52
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,559
Die now!

53
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,600
Die!

54
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,439
Die!

55
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:42,640
- Wait. Calm down.
- Let go of me!

56
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:47,000
Bro, calm down.

57
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,760
What's wrong with you?
You're going to kill him!

58
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:54,720
Calm down. You know he's crazy.

59
00:07:55,320 --> 00:07:58,520
If he dies, you'll become a murderer.

60
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,280
Damn it!

61
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,040
What's wrong with you?

62
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,480
- This way, please.
- Thank you.

63
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:41,840
Hello.

64
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,880
How are you?

65
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:51,199
I think you still look pale.

66
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,600
You should rest more.

67
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:09,239
My name is Phum Witassanai.

68
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:11,320
I brought you to the hospital.

69
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:15,359
Thank you.

70
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,079
May I ask your name?

71
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:19,039
I'll help you find your family.

72
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:21,560
They must be worried sick
about you by now.

73
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,240
I don't know.

74
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,600
What?

75
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,120
Well,

76
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:38,520
I don't remember my name.

77
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,720
My head hurts.

78
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:48,439
It's fine.

79
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:50,760
Don't force yourself,
or your headache will only get worse.

80
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:54,320
Please rest first then.

81
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:56,960
Mr. Phum.

82
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:02,400
Please don't leave me alone.

83
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:05,760
Please, Mr. Phum.

84
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,880
I'm begging you.

85
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:12,879
Please don't leave me, Mr. Phum.

86
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:16,719
Okay. I won't leave you
until your memory comes back.

87
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:18,959
But now, please rest.

88
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:21,200
Alright?

89
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:37,400
People like him never change.

90
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,960
Hey, madman.

91
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:59,200
You know something, don't you?

92
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:05,920
Who did you talk about?

93
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:09,480
What woman? What happened to her?

94
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:15,960
Woman... Woman...

95
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:20,000
Yeah, where did she go?

96
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:25,160
Sea...

97
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:29,200
The woman fell into the sea?

98
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,440
Someone...

99
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:38,999
threw her into the sea.

100
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,240
Woman...

101
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:43,880
Threw her into the sea?

102
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:46,360
Who threw her into the sea?

103
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:48,400
Hey.

104
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:49,880
Look at me.

105
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,280
Look at my face.

106
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,000
You know

107
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,960
who threw her into the sea, don't you?

108
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,360
Huh?

109
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,080
You know it, right?

110
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,960
Tell me!

111
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,800
Who threw that woman into the sea? Who?

112
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,960
Who threw that woman into the sea?

113
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,320
Who?

114
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:18,920
Pong?

115
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:22,239
Pong.

116
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,800
Calm down.

117
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,839
Wait.

118
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,760
Uh...

119
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:31,560
Hold this.

120
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,400
Hold it.

121
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,520
Don't.

122
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:49,040
Come here. Stay still.

123
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:50,999
Stay still.

124
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,240
Don't.

125
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:00,640
Done.

126
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,800
Hey.

127
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,560
Listen.

128
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:10,920
From now on,
don't go around running your mouth again.

129
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,640
Understand?

130
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:26,360
Thanks for bringing me to my senses, Piak.

131
00:13:27,160 --> 00:13:29,600
Otherwise, I might've killed him.

132
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:33,320
Come on, Piak. I'll buy you a drink.

133
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,359
- Yes, bro.
- Let's go.

134
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,720
Give that back to me.

135
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:58,280
Is something wrong?

136
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,280
There's something I need to tell you.

137
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:06,600
What is it?

138
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:17,040
About the time
Mr. Phum fell into the water.

139
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,680
You don't believe me?

140
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:45,199
It's not that I don't believe you.
I'm just surprised.

141
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,280
Mr. Phum is a good person.

142
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:50,160
Why would that woman want to hurt him?

143
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:52,320
I don't know.

144
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:55,279
And when we were
about to get in the car to leave,

145
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:58,800
I saw her standing right beside him.

146
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:03,400
So,

147
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:07,920
you mean she followed him?

148
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:10,600
I'm not sure.

149
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:14,680
But I don't want something terrible
to happen to Mr. Phum.

150
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,600
Sarai...

151
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:50,600
No.

152
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:53,280
Sarai.

153
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,120
Sarai, no.

154
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:00,520
Tell me!

155
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:03,040
I'm scared.

156
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:06,519
I don't know anything.

157
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:07,880
Tell me!

158
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:01,160
Hey. Hey.

159
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,560
Hey.

160
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,240
Hey.

161
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:10,759
Is something wrong, sir?

162
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:12,320
Her pulse has stopped.

163
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,480
Defibrillator is ready.

164
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,560
Defib, 200 joules.

165
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:43,119
200 joules.

166
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,160
200, oh!

167
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,440
Doctor.

168
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:00,440
How are you feeling?

169
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:05,400
I'm fine.

170
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:48,000
Hello.

171
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,919
Where's the Venerable Sir, Kang?

172
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:51,760
He's at his place.

173
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:56,839
I thought you had gone back
to Bangkok already, Mr. Narathon.

174
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:59,559
If you're still here, please come
have a meal at our house.

175
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:02,400
I want to repay you for helping Mook.

176
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,600
That's alright.

177
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:10,320
Please don't refuse.

178
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,320
If Mr. Narathon isn't available,

179
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:15,680
don't force him.

180
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:18,280
Dear...

181
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:23,119
Let's go meet the Venerable Sir.

182
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:24,959
I'm coming with you.

183
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:27,159
You kids wait here.

184
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,559
Why aren't they coming too?

185
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:33,279
Oh, come on. The place is tiny.

186
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:35,759
I don't want to bother him.

187
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:38,439
Just the two of us are enough. Come on.

188
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:39,999
Kang, could you lead the way?

189
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,800
Yes. This way, please.

190
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,519
Let's meet at the car later.

191
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:48,840
Dear, let's go.

192
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:04,839
The temple is so shady and peaceful.
I feel like taking a walk, Na.

193
00:22:04,840 --> 00:22:06,760
Sure. I'll go with you.

194
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:29,280
- How are you?
- How are you?

195
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:40,360
Shall we go take a walk over there?

196
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,680
Sure.

197
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,040
Yes?

198
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:25,960
On Skull Island, you were very brave.

199
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:30,360
Not really.

200
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:34,160
I'll confess that I was terrified.

201
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:37,759
Especially when I saw you,

202
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:41,440
Professor, and Da looking for me,

203
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:44,240
but none of you could see me.

204
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:48,000
I thought I wouldn't survive.

205
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:53,440
I was really scared then.

206
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:00,200
I was just as scared as you were.

207
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:19,160
I was scared of losing you.

208
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:41,560
Mook.

209
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:44,840
Let's go.

210
00:24:49,840 --> 00:24:52,959
Well, I have to go now.

211
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,400
Okay.

212
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:07,800
Let's go, Da.

213
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:50,400
How are you feeling?
Can you remember anything yet?

214
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,600
It feels like
I'm about to remember something,

215
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,120
but I still can't.

216
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:07,360
That's okay. I'll ask the police
to help find your family.

217
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:09,600
Not yet, please.

218
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:12,080
Please don't tell the police yet.

219
00:26:15,320 --> 00:26:16,280
Well...

220
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:19,720
I don't know what happened.

221
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:22,720
Please give me some time.

222
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:25,120
Then maybe I'll remember.

223
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:29,840
Don't trouble other people yet, please.

224
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:34,640
Please, Mr. Phum.

225
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:43,680
Alright.

226
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,199
<i>Why...</i>

227
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:48,959
<i>Why do this woman's eyes and smile look</i>

228
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:50,160
<i>so much like...?</i>

229
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,159
Hello.

230
00:27:09,160 --> 00:27:11,879
One cappuccino, please.

231
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:14,599
And one piece of orange cake.

232
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:15,640
Alright.

233
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:19,960
Oh, Mr. Phum.

234
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:23,879
Oh, Kaimook? Are you here alone?

235
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:26,520
I came with my family,
but they're waiting in the car.

236
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:28,839
Haven't you gone back
to Bangkok yet, Mr. Phum?

237
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:31,640
Not yet. There was a small accident.

238
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:33,960
Did you get hurt?

239
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:35,840
Not me.

240
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:39,640
Oh, Mr. Phum.

241
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:42,720
I have something to tell you.

242
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:46,080
But it'll take some time to explain.

243
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:51,200
Sure. How about this evening?

244
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:53,160
Okay.

245
00:28:31,840 --> 00:28:34,559
Hey.

246
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:37,320
You're grinning like a man in love.

247
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,360
I thought you'd never wake up.

248
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:44,879
You really sleep like there's no tomorrow.

249
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:48,600
I woke up a while ago, but I couldn't
find you, so I went back to sleep.

250
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:51,480
So what are you smiling about?

251
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:57,599
- Smiling?
- That dreamy smile on your face.

252
00:28:57,600 --> 00:29:00,680
Like a guy
who's fallen head over heels for a girl.

253
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,920
I think you're still half-asleep.

254
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:08,879
Go take a shower

255
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:10,640
so we can find something to eat.

256
00:29:17,040 --> 00:29:18,480
You changed the topic.

257
00:29:19,520 --> 00:29:20,720
That's definitely it.

258
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:25,320
Here's your hot porridge.

259
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:28,920
You need to eat plenty
so you'll recover quickly.

260
00:29:36,240 --> 00:29:37,640
You don't like porridge?

261
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:40,680
Oh.

262
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:42,480
Not that.

263
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:46,360
I love porridge.

264
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:50,080
I just don't like fried garlic.

265
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:02,680
You have to eat. I made this myself.

266
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:05,360
Or don't you like pork porridge?

267
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:10,120
I love pork porridge.
I just don't like fried garlic.

268
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,039
Then I'll get you another bowl.

269
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:14,280
No need.

270
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:18,120
Just pick the fried garlic out.

271
00:30:25,280 --> 00:30:29,000
Thank you, Mr. Phum. You're so good to me.

272
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:34,320
That's because I love you.

273
00:30:38,760 --> 00:30:41,519
Alright. There's no fried garlic now.

274
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:44,160
Eat it so you can take your medicine.

275
00:30:52,880 --> 00:30:54,320
Mr. Phum?

276
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:57,800
Mr. Phum?

277
00:31:01,400 --> 00:31:03,040
Then I'll get you another bowl.

278
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:04,920
No need.

279
00:31:05,960 --> 00:31:08,000
Just pick the fried garlic out.
That's enough.

280
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:15,560
Is something wrong?

281
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:18,000
Why are you looking at me like that?

282
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:22,000
Nothing.

283
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:40,600
You can eat it now.

284
00:31:41,760 --> 00:31:42,840
Thank you.

285
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:45,200
I'll be staying at a hotel tonight.

286
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:48,479
But I've hired a private nurse
to stay with you.

287
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:50,240
I'll come back tomorrow morning.

288
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:54,200
Thank you.

289
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:57,160
I won't trouble you for much longer.

290
00:31:58,800 --> 00:31:59,880
Don't worry about it.

291
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:03,840
Eat plenty, okay?
You'll regain your strength faster.

292
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,200
Alright.

293
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:23,560
Thank you.

294
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,960
Thank you.

295
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:43,400
Do you think Mr. Phum
will believe what I tell him?

296
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:47,440
I don't know.

297
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:51,280
But at least we'll have done our part.

298
00:32:52,120 --> 00:32:54,479
If something bad happens to him,

299
00:32:54,480 --> 00:32:56,200
we won't regret

300
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:58,400
keeping quiet when we knew something.

301
00:33:11,840 --> 00:33:13,639
It's chilly in here.

302
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:15,920
I'm going to the restroom. Are you going?

303
00:33:16,920 --> 00:33:19,920
Go ahead. I'll wait for Mr. Phum.

304
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:22,920
Okay. I'll be right back.

305
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:39,399
Hello, Kaimook.

306
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:41,239
I hope I'm not late.

307
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:43,239
Hello.

308
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:45,960
Not at all. I got here early.

309
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:50,160
But you arrived exactly on time.

310
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:52,879
You also brought a friend?

311
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:55,480
Yes, my friend went to the restroom.

312
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:00,039
Why don't we order while we talk?

313
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:02,640
Hopefully this isn't something
so serious that it'll ruin our appetites.

314
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:07,560
What's your friend's name?

315
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:09,839
Her name is Dara.

316
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:13,560
She's the one
who's going to tell you everything.

317
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:17,119
Dara? Oh, I remember her.

318
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:19,320
So what's this about?
Can you roughly tell me?

319
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,479
You'll love this restaurant.

320
00:35:04,480 --> 00:35:08,239
Well, the food is good.
The service is good too.

321
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:09,239
How do you know?

322
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,240
Well.

323
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:12,680
I've been here before.

324
00:35:14,760 --> 00:35:16,080
With who?

325
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:21,920
You must've come here with a girl before.

326
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:24,719
- You're talking nonsense.
- What nonsense?

327
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:27,479
Back then you two probably
couldn't stand each other.

328
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:30,959
You know, like every hero and heroine.
They start out as rivals

329
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:33,160
and end up as lovers.

330
00:35:34,040 --> 00:35:37,720
- You never stop imagining things, do you?
- Wait.

331
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:41,199
Now I'm really curious

332
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:43,360
to see this lucky girl.

333
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:56,559
Fine then. Let's order something first.

334
00:35:56,560 --> 00:35:58,400
Let's take a look.

335
00:36:00,240 --> 00:36:02,440
- The seafood here is good.
- I see.

336
00:36:05,440 --> 00:36:07,600
Hey? Aren't we going in?

337
00:36:10,560 --> 00:36:11,439
Let's eat somewhere else.

338
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:13,880
Hey, Thon? Thon?

339
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:28,160
Dara's back.

340
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:29,920
Hello, Dara.

341
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:31,639
Hello.

342
00:36:31,640 --> 00:36:34,480
Kaimook told me you had something
you wanted to tell me.

343
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:37,359
Sit down, Da.

344
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:40,400
And tell him everything.

345
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:49,040
Mr. Phum, I...

346
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:02,080
What's wrong, Da?

347
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:04,920
Da?

348
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:09,760
I... I have a headache.

349
00:37:10,480 --> 00:37:11,639
Please excuse me.

350
00:37:11,640 --> 00:37:12,920
Wait, Da.

351
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:17,000
Mr. Phum came all the way here.
What's gotten into you?

352
00:37:19,200 --> 00:37:20,440
I really don't feel well.

353
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:22,640
I'm sorry.

354
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:24,839
Wait, Da.

355
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:28,200
Please excuse me. I'm sorry.

356
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:50,880
Da.

357
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:55,360
What's wrong with you?

358
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:02,600
Nothing.

359
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:06,000
What happened?

360
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:13,880
That woman ghost
is around here, isn't she?

361
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:17,800
Is she, Da?

362
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:21,800
You couldn't tell Mr. Phum
because you're scared, right?

363
00:38:27,720 --> 00:38:30,720
Yes. That woman ghost came after me again.

364
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:32,840
Now will you let me go home?

365
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:50,760
Mr. Narathon.

366
00:39:54,680 --> 00:39:57,040
I didn't think I'd run into you here.

367
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:00,640
I never thought
I'd run into you here either.

368
00:40:02,560 --> 00:40:04,160
You finished dinner pretty quickly.

369
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:05,880
Yes?

370
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:10,040
Didn't you just
have dinner with my father?

371
00:40:11,720 --> 00:40:15,279
Yes. Da and I
had arranged to meet Mr. Phum.

372
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:16,800
You saw us?

373
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:21,200
I didn't see Ms. Da.

374
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:25,560
It might be when she was in the restroom.

375
00:40:30,720 --> 00:40:33,360
I'm really glad I ran into you.

376
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:46,880
There's something
I'd like your advice about.

377
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:49,400
Are you free?

378
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:52,560
I am.

379
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:08,000
Da.

380
00:41:09,240 --> 00:41:10,200
What's wrong?

381
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:13,440
I only called your name
and you jumped out of your skin.

382
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:17,240
I was lost in thought.

383
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:23,840
Where's Mook? Didn't you go out with her?

384
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:27,000
She'll be back soon.

385
00:41:28,480 --> 00:41:31,959
Na, why is the house so quiet?

386
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:33,680
Where is everyone?

387
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:36,599
Dad and Mom went to visit the temple.

388
00:41:36,600 --> 00:41:38,040
They're going to
stop by the market afterward.

389
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:39,640
Temple?

390
00:41:41,920 --> 00:41:43,160
Venerable Sir.

391
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:46,279
Na, let's go to the temple.

392
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,840
Why?

393
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:54,720
Oh, I know. You want to check
an auspicious wedding date, don't you?

394
00:41:55,800 --> 00:41:57,480
No.

395
00:41:58,280 --> 00:42:01,279
I'll explain in the car, okay?
Come on, hurry.

396
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:02,240
Let's go.

397
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:07,200
That means

398
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:09,640
that woman ghost

399
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:13,040
wants to hurt my father?

400
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:21,559
Da told me the way she looked at Mr. Phum...

401
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:24,119
There was so much hatred
and resentment in her eyes.

402
00:42:24,120 --> 00:42:25,440
It was terrifying.

403
00:42:27,040 --> 00:42:29,840
That's why I wanted
Mr. Phum to be aware of it.

404
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:39,840
Is something wrong?

405
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:44,720
Do you remember
when I pulled my father out of the water?

406
00:42:48,120 --> 00:42:49,920
Who went down to save me?

407
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:52,280
I did.

408
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:57,200
Did you see anyone else?

409
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:01,080
It sounded like
he thought someone else was there.

410
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:06,160
But at the time,
I didn't think much of it.

411
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:13,280
Does that mean
Mr. Phum saw that woman ghost too?

412
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:17,480
I'm not sure.

413
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,360
What are you going to do now?

414
00:43:22,760 --> 00:43:24,000
I have to find out

415
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:26,600
who that woman is

416
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:30,159
and why she hates my father so much

417
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:32,200
that she's trying to kill him.

418
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:49,799
I used to think ghosts
weren't real either.

419
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:51,679
But after experiencing it myself,

420
00:43:51,680 --> 00:43:54,600
it's honestly unbelievable.

421
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:01,559
There are many things in this world

422
00:44:01,560 --> 00:44:04,079
that seem impossible,

423
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:05,640
yet they happen.

424
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:10,080
That woman ghost who follows you, Dara,

425
00:44:11,200 --> 00:44:13,760
and the pirate ghosts on the island...

426
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:18,080
all remain trapped in a cycle of karma.

427
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:25,720
Everything is almost
at its appointed time.

428
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:34,440
What time, Venerable Sir?

429
00:44:50,680 --> 00:44:52,480
Do not use it to harm anyone.

430
00:44:53,320 --> 00:44:56,840
Wear it only for protection.

431
00:44:58,400 --> 00:44:59,480
Yes, Venerable Sir.

432
00:45:37,800 --> 00:45:38,799
I'm worried about you.

433
00:45:38,800 --> 00:45:41,759
And I'm afraid that woman
might come after you.

434
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:43,559
I don't think I can promise you that.

435
00:45:43,560 --> 00:45:45,960
- Why not?
- Because I'm worried about you too.

436
00:45:49,400 --> 00:45:51,680
<i>I have to find out</i>

437
00:45:52,320 --> 00:45:54,120
who ordered my murder.

438
00:45:55,280 --> 00:45:56,919
You've remembered everything,
haven't you, Sompong?

439
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:58,040
I remember!

440
00:46:01,240 --> 00:46:04,560
You shameless woman.
How dare you steal my husband!

441
00:46:06,080 --> 00:46:07,800
You dared to slap me?

442
00:46:37,400 --> 00:46:39,640
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
